00:00:05,333 --> 00:00:09,096
April 4, 1953

4
00:00:24,549 --> 00:00:26,786
We have a new student
in class today.

5
00:00:26,786 --> 00:00:28,276
His name's Robert.

6
00:00:28,276 --> 00:00:30,805
And he's just moved 
here from st. Louis.

7
00:00:31,036 --> 00:00:32,854
Since he's coming on late,

8
00:00:32,854 --> 00:00:34,539
he'll need a study buddy.

9
00:00:35,383 --> 00:00:36,999
Any volunteers?

10
00:00:38,766 --> 00:00:39,739
Hmm?

11
00:00:42,145 --> 00:00:44,490
That's swell,
Norman, thank you.

12
00:00:44,711 --> 00:00:46,190
Now, uh,

13
00:00:46,190 --> 00:00:50,149
I gather you're all curious what 
brings Robert to Philadelphia, so...

14
00:00:50,149 --> 00:00:51,059
Robert?

15
00:00:52,749 --> 00:00:54,151
Go ahead, son.

16
00:01:01,826 --> 00:01:04,376
My daddy's got a new job.

17
00:01:04,376 --> 00:01:06,091
We had to move.

18
00:01:06,613 --> 00:01:08,543
He's in a band.

19
00:01:09,347 --> 00:01:12,042
There's a club here
wants him to play.

20
00:01:12,042 --> 00:01:13,837
I got one of his records.

21
00:01:16,894 --> 00:01:18,486
That's him there.

22
00:01:18,486 --> 00:01:20,038
He plays drums.

23
00:01:20,038 --> 00:01:21,794
Is he gonna be on bandstand?

24
00:01:21,794 --> 00:01:23,940
Does he know Perry Como?

25
00:01:23,940 --> 00:01:25,823
I don't think so, but...

26
00:01:25,823 --> 00:01:28,665
he jammed with Louis Armstrong once.

27
00:01:30,171 --> 00:01:32,100
Mr. Garvey,

28
00:01:32,100 --> 00:01:34,737
if Norman doesn't want to 
be his study buddy, I will.

29
00:01:34,737 --> 00:01:36,534
No way! You didn't raise your hand.

30
00:01:36,534 --> 00:01:38,050
Neither did you, fatso.

31
00:01:38,050 --> 00:01:42,129
Now, now, there's plenty of time
for everyone to get to know Robert.

32
00:01:44,009 --> 00:01:45,692
Good morning, children.

33
00:01:47,613 --> 00:01:49,974
Sorry to interrupt, Mr. Garvey,
but there's been a...

34
00:01:49,974 --> 00:01:51,444
a mix-up.

35
00:01:51,444 --> 00:01:54,387
Robert. Get your things
and come with me.

36
00:01:56,188 --> 00:01:57,586
What's all this?

37
00:01:59,819 --> 00:02:02,236
- The boy's at the wrong school.
- I don't understand.

38
00:02:02,236 --> 00:02:03,947
Elliot, look at him.

39
00:02:03,947 --> 00:02:05,201
What's it matter?
He gets along well...

40
00:02:05,201 --> 00:02:06,640
It matters plenty.

41
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:07,903
Now, don't go making trouble.

42
00:02:07,903 --> 00:02:09,786
I wouldn't want to
lose my best teacher.

43
00:02:09,786 --> 00:02:11,029
Robert.

44
00:03:11,657 --> 00:03:13,271
Name's Howard Garvey.

45
00:03:13,271 --> 00:03:15,164
He's seeing this
court-ordered shrink.

46
00:03:15,164 --> 00:03:16,792
Of course they get to 
talking about his father.

47
00:03:16,792 --> 00:03:17,945
And?

48
00:03:17,945 --> 00:03:22,153
The guy always heard his dad 
was a drunk, deserted the family.

49
00:03:23,689 --> 00:03:24,878
Find out something new?

50
00:03:24,878 --> 00:03:30,186
Yeah. The truth is, he was 
killed in Fairmount park, 1953.

51
00:03:30,186 --> 00:03:32,368
Huh. So why the cover story?

52
00:03:32,368 --> 00:03:35,225
Well, he's in my office, Lil.
You can ask him yourself.

53
00:03:35,722 --> 00:03:37,667
I'll, uh, grab Scotty.

54
00:03:46,331 --> 00:03:47,576
You can't be here.

55
00:03:47,576 --> 00:03:49,162
Nice to see you too, Lil.

56
00:03:49,162 --> 00:03:50,990
Yeah, you can't be here.

57
00:03:51,414 --> 00:03:54,286
- I just want to talk.
- Christina.

58
00:04:04,762 --> 00:04:06,554
Boss has something.

59
00:04:09,888 --> 00:04:12,027
I don't put a lot of stock
in head doctors,

60
00:04:12,027 --> 00:04:13,200
but I'm under orders.

61
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:15,752
And this guy had to check
my family's medical history.

62
00:04:15,752 --> 00:04:17,075
For emotional disorders.

63
00:04:17,075 --> 00:04:19,348
Depression, whatever.

64
00:04:19,794 --> 00:04:21,663
I guess it's hereditary.

65
00:04:22,835 --> 00:04:26,032
Or you thought maybe
your dad had it, too?

66
00:04:26,032 --> 00:04:27,048
Yeah.

67
00:04:27,351 --> 00:04:31,105
But if he did, well, that beat-down
in the park got him first.

68
00:04:31,105 --> 00:04:34,282
Why do you think your mom
kept the murder a secret?

69
00:04:34,282 --> 00:04:35,527
Don't know.

70
00:04:36,106 --> 00:04:41,517
But the medical examiner's
report is clear-cut.

71
00:04:43,545 --> 00:04:44,830
You, um...

72
00:04:45,009 --> 00:04:47,185
have an accident, Howard?

73
00:04:50,094 --> 00:04:51,159
No.

74
00:04:52,024 --> 00:04:55,504
That was me.
That's why the court-ordered doc.

75
00:04:55,720 --> 00:04:57,660
What does your family say
about your dad now?

76
00:04:57,660 --> 00:04:59,630
Called my mom for the 
first time in 15 years,

77
00:04:59,630 --> 00:05:02,500
see if maybe dad wasn't
a bum, after all. / And?

78
00:05:02,500 --> 00:05:05,638
Said she'd call me back
after cribbage.

79
00:05:05,638 --> 00:05:07,341
That was last week.

80
00:05:07,341 --> 00:05:08,791
Got any siblings?

81
00:05:08,791 --> 00:05:10,643
A brother. Dean.

82
00:05:11,089 --> 00:05:13,705
Lost his number, long time back.

83
00:05:15,345 --> 00:05:18,773
I don't even know
where my dad is buried.

84
00:05:20,182 --> 00:05:22,620
If we do this, Howard,

85
00:05:22,620 --> 00:05:24,947
we're gonna need you around.

86
00:05:26,393 --> 00:05:28,327
I'm not going anywhere.

87
00:05:30,115 --> 00:05:31,963
Sure about that?

88
00:05:36,601 --> 00:05:38,362
I'm sure.

